text = "[b]How To Play[/b]

Hotpot is a 4-player Tabletop Card Game. The Card Deck consists of 96 Cards, each player starts with 8 Cards on their hand.

The objective is to create three sets of three cards each. Sets can be made with either a [b]Three-of-a-Kind[/b] Set (3 identical cards of the same ingredient) or a [b]Category Set[/b] (3 cards of the same color category but with unique ingredients).

In the center section of the hotpot table, you’ll see the draw and discard piles - the cards here are available for anyone to draw from during their turn.

Turns are played in a counter-clockwise order starting with the player first on the table. On the beginning of their turn the player must draw a card: either from the draw pile (blind draw), or the topmost of any of the other players discard piles. The player may not choose a card from their own discard pile. The player must end their turn with 8 cards, and therefore must discard one card facing up on top of their discard pile. Then the next player’s turn begins.

When a player holds three sets on their hand, they have won the game."

